Problem: Top K Frequent Elements
Topic: Arrays, HashMap, Sorting
Difficulty: Medium

Approach:
Use a hash map to count the frequency of each element. Store each element as a pair (frequency, value) in a vector, sort the vector in descending order of frequency, and return the first k elements.

Time Complexity: O(n + m log m), where m is the number of unique elements
Space Complexity: O(m)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> topKFrequent(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.size();
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;

        for(int x:nums){
            mp[x]++;
        }

        vector<pair<int,int>> freq;
        for(auto it:mp){
            freq.push_back({it.second,it.first});
        }
        
        sort(freq.rbegin(),freq.rend());
        vector<int> ans;
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
           ans.push_back(freq[i].second);
        }

    return ans;
    }
};
